    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Like the attack ads he defends, Roger Stone's Feb. 26 Op-Ed piece, "Positively Negative," contains a myopic truth while losing sight of a critical  point. Neither attack ads nor so-called positive ads truly inform the public. The first present candidates as their opponents would prefer to see them. The second present candidates as they would prefer to be seen.</p>
      </block>
